This workshop is the second of a new series . The first WebDB workshop was held in Valencia , Spain in conjunction with the EDBT'98 conference and was a great success both by the quality of its papers and its number of attendees . The proceedings were published by Springer Verlag , as part of the Lecture Notes in Computer Science ( LNCS ) series . _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ TOPICS OF INTEREST ( a non-exclusive list ) _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ - data models for the Web ; - query languages and systems for Web data ; - query languages and systems for XML ; - semistructured data management and the Web ; - management of Web documents ; - finding structure in Web information ; - data integration over the Web ; - warehousing of Web data ; - data-intensive applications on the Web ; - methodologies and tools for Web data publishing ; - mining , exploring and visualizing the Web ; - transactions on the Web ; - security and integrity issues ; _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ SUBMISSION GUIDELINES _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ Authors are invited to submit an extended abstract not exceeding 6 pages ( single-spaced , 10 pt minimum , approximately 3000 words ) by March 1 , 1999 . Electronic submissions are required . Please send an e-mail containing your submission in postscript or HTML format to : webdb 99 @ ivt . eiwg . yyc Authors intending to submit a paper are invited to send an e-mail of interest by February 22 , 1999 to the address above , containing title , authors and a short abstract ( 100 words ) of the paper . Papers accepted for presentation will be included in the informal proceedings to be distributed at the Workshop , and put up on the Workshop Web site . _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ IMPORTANT DATES _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ - E- mail of Interest by : February , 22 - Submission Deadline : March , 1 - Notification : April , 5 - Final Version : April , 26 - Workshop : June 3 / 4 ( right after SIGMOD ) _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ ATTENDANCE _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ _ Authors of accepted papers will be expected to present their papers at the workshop .
